The feast of divine Mercy sunday comes up on the second sunday after Easter. It is a great and special day in which God pours out his mercy on mankind for the sake of the sorrowful passion of his son JESUS CHRIST.
It is a day we celbrate the special mercy of God on humanity.

It is marked by special activities on the day. Meanwhile before the sunday some things are done in preparation . 
These includes:-
The divine mercy Novena
the acts of mercy both coporal and spiritual works of mercy.
Reparations for the sins of the world.
